# see https://github.com/BurntSushi/ripgrep/blob/master/GUIDE.md#configuration-file
#
# be careful /w sorting; search for this sentence under --sort flag in man pages:
#  "Note that sorting results currently always forces ripgrep to abandon parallelism and run in a single thread."
############################################

# Don't let ripgrep vomit really long lines to my terminal, and show a preview.
--max-columns=150
--max-columns-preview

# Add my 'web' type.
#--type-add
#web:*.{html,css,js}*

# Using glob patterns to include/exclude files or folders
#--glob=!git/*

# Set the colors.
#--colors=line:none
#--colors=line:style:bold

# Because who cares about case!?
--smart-case

# Suppress all error messages related to opening and reading files:
--no-messages

# follow symlinks
--follow

# search hidden files
--hidden

# search in compressed files
--search-zip

# for some reason not reproing for me anymore, but apparently some git config
# (eg ignored files) might not be picked up if said conf is included via [include]
# tags; in those cases see https://github.com/BurntSushi/ripgrep/issues/1014#issuecomment-626752654
#--ignore-file=$git_global_exclude_file_memoize
